NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ibm.sid, ibm.version FROM Internet_Base_Model ibm JOIN (SELECT sid, version, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rnk FROM Internet_Base_Model GROUP BY sid, version) ranked ON ibm.sid = ranked.sid AND ibm.version = ranked.version WHERE ranked.rnk = 1;

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Given the following database schema, write a SQL query to answer the question below.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: WITH VersionCounts AS (SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS usage_count FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version), RankedVersions AS (SELECT sid, version, usage_count, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY usage_count DESC) AS rnk FROM VersionCounts) SELECT sid, version FROM RankedVersions WHERE rnk = 1;

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ms.sid FROM ModelServices ms JOIN BaseModel bm ON ms.bmid = bm.bmid JOIN AgentCreator ac ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid JOIN User u ON ac.uid = u.uid WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh' GROUP BY ms.sid HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ms.bmid) = (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT bmid) FROM BaseModel bm2 JOIN AgentCreator ac2 ON bm2.creator_uid = ac2.uid JOIN User u2 ON ac2.uid = u2.uid WHERE u2.username = 'user_iuwrh');

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel cm LEFT JOIN ModelConfigurations mc ON cm.bmid = mc.bmid AND cm.mid = mc.mid WHERE mc.mid IS NULL;
